\begin_layout Standard
To confirm that the performance differences observed in Section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:ExpResults"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 are statistically significant rather than artifacts of run-to-run variability,
 a nonparametric statistical analysis was conducted on the 30 final objective values obtained by each method on the full benchmark formulation (
\begin_inset Formula $ALL$
\end_inset

) across all five dimensions.
 The Friedman test was applied independently at each dimension to assess whether the ten methods produce significantly different rank distributions.
 Pairwise comparisons were then performed using Wilcoxon signed-rank tests with Holm correction to control the family-wise error rate.
 Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:friedman"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 reports the mean Friedman ranks for each method at each dimension,
 together with the overall average rank and the Friedman test p-values.
\end_layout

